<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4379: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-29T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                        1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mission requests you be informed it has been carefully considering the
                            advisability of a provisional recognition of the <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> Government and desires to know
                            whether, in view of the success attending the arms of the Omsk
                            Government during the past month, you are disposed to modify your views
                            regarding such recognition as expressed in your telegram to Department
                            April 12, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>